HEADWORD: Quica
<hw>Qui"ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the native
Brazilian name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small South American
opossum (<spn>Didelphys quica</spn>), native of Guiana and Brazil. It
feeds upon insects, small birds, and fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

